CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley. Upper right: Rev. Talley seated in front of members of his Young Ladies' Usher Board...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fifteen women wearing light colored dresses, posed with Rev. Cornell E. Talley in front of American flag, ferns, and "Welcome" fringed banner, in Central Baptist Church for banquet honoring Talley
